%% Per-task split — 70/15/15 with TEST OFF-LIMITS
flowchart LR
    DATA[(Task data<br/>n rows total)] --> SPLIT[data/splits.py<br/>seed=42]
    SPLIT --> TRAIN[TRAIN — 70%<br/>X_train, y_train]
    SPLIT --> VAL[VAL — 15%<br/>X_val, y_val]
    SPLIT --> TEST[TEST — 15%<br/>X_test, y_test<br/>===========================<br/>TEST OFF-LIMITS<br/>until final_report.py<br/>===========================]

    TRAIN --> RUN[framework/runner.py<br/>run_one]
    VAL --> RUN
    RUN --> SCORE[composite = min(val, train)<br/>- 0.05 * |val - train|]
    SCORE --> HC[framework/hill_climb.py<br/>25 iters × 5 backbones]
    HC --> CHAMP[best_config.json]
    CHAMP --> FR[framework/final_report.py<br/>ONE-SHOT REFIT]
    TRAIN --> FR
    VAL --> FR
    TEST -->|"reads X_test, y_test<br/>ONCE per task"| FR
    FR --> FINAL[final_report.json<br/>test_score<br/>delta_vs_dsbench]

